Our entrepreneurial spirit, hands-on environment, and fast-paced culture encourage employees to be their best, bringing innovative solutions to reach the skincare professional and consumer. We are highly energetic, passionate, and results-oriented. You will find that Dermalogica is a very special place, with tremendous opportunities ahead for us, all building upon a record of achievement. 
 
 
Dermalogica is seeking a dynamic  Director of Digital Disruption  to help drive continued modernization of the organization through custom web technologies and data-driven personalization. The role will be responsible for leading a small group of designers and developers to build and scale AI-powered web technologies for the premier global skincare business. 
 
This opening presents you with a fantastic opportunity to revolutionize the industry by building world-class digital innovation capabilities within Dermalogica. The ideal individual will possess exceptional technical strengths, with the ability to architect, scale, and maintain web technologies independent from the IT Department. The position is based at the corporate headquarters in Carson, California, and will report directly to the CEO. 
 
 
Required Experience and Skills: 
 
 Entrepreneurial mindset with a passion for the digital world and its implication on business 
 Deep knowledge of how modern web browsers work. Must:
 Be able to navigate the DOM 
 Understand how JavaScript executes and what its limitations are 
 Understand the limitations of different browsers on different devices 
 Systems Architecture
 Must have deep knowledge of the role different systems play up and down a modern web stack, and how to optimize systems architecture for scale. 
 Dev Ops
 Must have at least a basic understanding of how to host and scale on the cloud. 
 API Architecture
 Must be able to architect/write modern RESTful APIs 
 Database Architecture
 Must have basic-to-advanced knowledge of relational databases and/or a NoSQL approach 
 Data Wrangling
 Must be able to wrangle and clean data using SQL and a scripting language such as Python 
 Statistical Awareness
 Must have moderate-to-advanced knowledge of Statistics 
 Must understand machine learning and artificial intelligence. 
 UX Design Awareness
 Must understand the fundamentals of modern UX Design. Enough awareness to recognize strong design and work closely with strong UX Designers. 
 Preferred Attributes: 
 
 Master‚Äôs Degree or higher in Computer Science, Machine Learning, AI, Data Science or related 
 Successful track record as a Software Engineer  a definite plus 
 Ability to manage, mentor, and develop a team  highly desirable 
 Advanced capability to analyze and manipulate image data in Python using statistical and image-specific libraries 
 Advanced capabilities with Dev Ops 
 
 
